quran[98]{c,v,t}:
  19,1,H.Y.A.S. (Kaf. Ha. Ya. Ain. Sud)
  19,2,(This is) a reminder of your Master’s mercy to His servant Zachariah
  19,3,"When he called his Master, a private calling"
  19,4,"He said: my Master, indeed my bones have weakened and my head has turned white (from old age), and I have not been unhappy about praying to you, my Master"
  19,5,"And indeed I am afraid of my relatives after me (when I am dead), and my wife is infertile, so give me an heir from Yourself"
  19,6,"to inherit from me and inherit from Jacob’s family. And my Master, make him pleasing"
  19,7,"(He was told): Zachariah, indeed We give you good news of a boy, his name is Yahya (John the Baptist), We did not give anyone his name (or attribute) in the past"
  19,8,"He said: my Master, how can there be a son for me while my wife is infertile and I have reached the very old age"
  19,9,"He (the angel) said: it is so, your Master says: it is easy for Me, and I have created you in the past while you were nothing"
  19,10,"He said: my Master, give me a sign. He said: your sign is that you will not speak to the people for three nights (being) sound (and healthy)"
  19,11,"So he went out of the chamber (place of prayer) to his people, and revealed to them (by sign language) to glorify (God) morning and evening"
  19,12,"Yahya, take the book firmly. And We gave him the wisdom from childhood"
  19,13,"and sympathy and purity (and integrity) from Us, and he was in control of himself"
  19,14,"and good (and kind) to his parent, and he was not a disobeying bully"
  19,15,And peace (and well-being) upon him the day he was born and the day he dies and the day he is raised to life
  19,16,"And mention Mary in the book, when she withdrew from her family to an eastern place"
  19,17,"She took a partition (to separate herself) from them, then We sent Our spirit (Gabriel) to her, and he looked like a perfect human being to her"
  19,18,"She said: I look for protection of the beneficent from you, if you control yourself (then get away from me)"
  19,19,"He said: I am only a messenger of your Master to present you a pure (and righteous) boy"
  19,20,"She said: how can I have a son while no man has ever touched me, and I was not unchaste"
  19,21,"He said: so it is, your Master says: it is easy for Me, and We make him a sign for the people and a mercy from Us, and it is a matter already decided"
  19,22,"So she conceived him, and withdrew to a remote place with him"
  19,23,"The pain of childbirth drove her to trunk of the palm tree. She said: I wish I was dead before this and I was completely forgotten"
  19,24,"Then (a voice) called her from under her that do not be sad, your Master has placed a stream under you"
  19,25,And shake trunk of the palm tree towards you and it drops fresh ripe dates on you
  19,26,"So eat and drink and be cheerful. If you see any human being, then say: indeed I pledged a fast for the beneficent, so I never talk to any human being today"
  19,27,"Then she brought him to her people, carrying him. They said: Mary, you have committed an unprecedented thing"
  19,28,"Sister of Aaron, your father was not a bad man and your mother was not unchaste"
  19,29,"Then she pointed to him. They said: how can we talk to any child who is the cradle"
  19,30,"He said: indeed I am God’s servant, He gave me the book and made me a prophet"
  19,31,"and He made me blessed wherever I am, and He instructed me to the mandatory prayer and the mandatory charity as long as I live"
  19,32,"and good (and kind) to my mother, and He did not make me a miserable bully"
  19,33,"And peace (and well-being) upon me on a day I was born, and a day that I die, and a day I am raised to life"
  19,34,"That is (the story of) Jesus, son of Mary, a true word that they doubt about it"
  19,35,"It is not for God to take a child, He is flawless. When He decides on an issue, then He just says for it: be, and it will be"
  19,36,"And (Jesus said): indeed God is my Master and your Master, so serve Him, this is straight path"
  19,37,"Then the groups disagreed among themselves, so woe to those who disbelieved in seeing the great day (the resurrection day)"
  19,38,How well they hear and see on a day they come to Us! But today the wrongdoers are in obvious error
  19,39,"And warn them of day of the regret, when the issue is decided while they are in negligence and they do not believe"
  19,40,Indeed We inherit the earth and whoever is on it and they are returned to Us
  19,41,"And mention Abraham in the book, he was a truthful prophet"
  19,42,"When he said to his father: my father, why do you serve that which does not hear and does not see and is of no use to you at all"
  19,43,"My father, indeed some of the knowledge has come to me that did not come to you, so follow me, I guide you to a proper path"
  19,44,"My father, do not serve Satan, indeed Satan is rebellious against the beneficent"
  19,45,"My father, I am afraid that a punishment from the beneficent touches you, so you will be a friend of Satan"
  19,46,"He said: Abraham, do you hate my gods? If you do not stop, I shall stone you, and get away from me for a long while"
  19,47,"He said: peace (and well-being) upon you, I am going to ask forgiveness for you from my Master, indeed he is kind to me"
  19,48,"I stay away from you and what you call on other than God, and I call on my Master, perhaps I will not be unhappy with prayer to my Master"
  19,49,"So when he stayed away from them and what they served other than God, We gave him Isaac and Jacob, and We made each of them a prophet"
  19,50,"And We gave them from Our mercy, and We gave them a true and high fame"
  19,51,"And mention Moses in the book. Indeed he was devoted, and he was a messenger and a prophet"
  19,52,"And We called him from the right side of the mountain (Mount Sinai), and made him close for a private talk"
  19,53,"And We gave him from Our mercy his brother Aaron, a prophet"
  19,54,And mention Ishmael in the book. Indeed he was true to the promise and he was a messenger and a prophet
  19,55,"And he used to order his family to the mandatory prayer and the mandatory charity, and he was pleasing in his Master's view"
  19,56,And mention Idris (Enoch) in the book. Indeed he was a truthful prophet
  19,57,And We raised him to an elevated position
  19,58,"They are those whom God favored upon them among the prophets from descendant of Adam and from those whom We carried with Noah (in the Ark) and from descendant of Abraham and Israel (Jacob), and from those whom We guided and We chose. When signs of the beneficent were read to them, they fell down prostrating (being humble) and crying"
  19,59,"Then successors succeeded after them who eliminated (and neglected) the mandatory prayer and followed their desires, so they will face (the result) of (being) wrong"
  19,60,"Except anyone who repented, and believed and did good work, then they enter the garden and will not be wronged a bit"
  19,61,Eternal gardens which the beneficent promised His servants as the unseen. Indeed His promise is coming
  19,62,"They do not hear any useless (talk) in there, but only peace (and well-being), and they have their provision (and food) in it, morning and evening (and all through the day)"
  19,63,This is the garden that We leave to Our servants who control themselves
  19,64,"And we (angels) do not come down except by your Master's command, whatever in front of us and whatever behind us and whatever between that belongs to Him. And your Master is not forgetful"
  19,65,"(He is) Master of the skies and the earth and whatever between them, so serve Him and be persistent in His servitude. Do you know anyone with the same name (or attributes) as Him"
  19,66,"And the human being says: will I be brought back to life after I am dead"
  19,67,Or does the human being not remember that We created him in the past while he was nothing
  19,68,"And by your Master, We shall gather them and the devils then We shall bring them in attendance around hell on their knees"
  19,69,Then We shall pick out from every group those of them who were more unruly against the beneficent
  19,70,"And We certainly know better those who deserve it, entering (and burning)"
  19,71,And there is not any of you that will not arrive at it. This is an unavoidable decision of your Master
  19,72,"Then We save those who controlled themselves, and We leave the wrongdoers in it on their knees"
  19,73,"And when Our clear signs are read to them, those who disbelieved say to those who believed: which one of the two groups is in better position and in better company"
  19,74,And We destroyed many generations before them who were better in assets and in appearance
  19,75,"Say: anyone who is in error, then the beneficent extends an extension to him, until when they see what they are promised, either the punishment or the hour (of resurrection), then they are going to know who is in a worse position and weaker in forces"
  19,76,And God increases guidance of those who are guided. And the lasting good works has a better reward with your Master and has a better return
  19,77,"Did you see the one who disbelieved in Our signs and said: I will certainly be given wealth and children"
  19,78,Did he know the unseen or did he take a promise from the beneficent
  19,79,"Not at all, We are going to write what he says, and We extend an extension for him from the punishment"
  19,80,And We inherit from him whatever he says and he comes to Us individually
  19,81,And they took gods other than God to be (source of) power (and honor) for them
  19,82,"Not at all, they are going to deny their servitude, and will be an adversary against them"
  19,83,Did you not see that We sent the devils to the disbelievers to encourage them with encouragement
  19,84,"So do not be in a hurry against them, We only count a number for them"
  19,85,A day that We gather those who controlled themselves as a delegation to the beneficent
  19,86,and We are going to drive the guilty ones to hell in thirst
  19,87,They do not have power of the mediation except anyone who took a promise from the beneficent
  19,88,"And they said: the beneficent took a child"
  19,89,You have certainly committed a horrible thing
  19,90,And the skies are about to tear from it and the earth is about to split wide open and the mountains are about to fall down collapsing
  19,91,that they designate a child to the beneficent
  19,92,It is not becoming for the beneficent to take a child
  19,93,Everyone in the skies and the earth only come to the beneficent as servant
  19,94,He has certainly taken them into account and has counted their number
  19,95,And each of them comes to the resurrection day individually
  19,96,Indeed the beneficent is going to put love (and friendship) for those who believed and did good works
  19,97,"So We only made it (Quran) easy in your language, for you to give good news to those who control themselves with it, and to warn contentious (and hostile) people with it"
  19,98,And We destroyed many generations before them. Do you feel any one of them or hear any sound from them